485
00:32:24,530 --> 00:32:28,182
Those messages that you brought us from my late husband.

486
00:32:28,182 --> 00:32:32,851
You couldn't possibly know this,
but they've changed everything.

487
00:32:32,851 --> 00:32:36,149
- Ah, what're you talking about?
- Oh, please.

488
00:32:36,149 --> 00:32:38,315
Come, I want you.. I want you to meet someone.

489
00:32:38,315 --> 00:32:40,526
I want you to meet my son's fiance.

490
00:32:41,397 --> 00:32:44,699
Michael.
This is Monica.

491
00:32:44,699 --> 00:32:49,683
Hi, nice to meet you.

492
00:32:52,178 --> 00:32:56,002
Tell them you need to use the bathroom.
Do it.

493
00:33:03,875 --> 00:33:06,200
You looked puzzled out there.

494
00:33:07,616 --> 00:33:11,868
You knew her. Monica,
you knew that woman, didn't you?

495
00:33:11,868 --> 00:33:15,370
Run some water.
They can't hear me,
but they can hear you.

496
00:33:17,389 --> 00:33:20,844
She killed you, didn't she?
You and her had a thing.

497
00:33:20,844 --> 00:33:23,567
- She killed you.
- Do you like that story?

498
00:33:23,567 --> 00:33:27,590
Me? Personally,
I prefer the Henry Alonso's story.

499
00:33:27,590 --> 00:33:29,319
Yeah, that's a great story.

500
00:33:29,319 --> 00:33:32,350
You got a sympathetic victim.
Me.

501
00:33:32,350 --> 00:33:36,617
You have a villain, we can all rule against

502
00:33:36,617 --> 00:33:39,660
unemployed drug addict with a criminal record.

503
00:33:40,737 --> 00:33:44,174
And we have the added
bonus of your involvement.

504
00:33:44,174 --> 00:33:47,823
No small thing as far as
my wife's concerned.

505
00:33:47,823 --> 00:33:50,090
I'm asking you a direct question.

506
00:33:50,090 --> 00:33:53,494
Henry Alonso killed me.
You close the case.

507
00:33:53,494 --> 00:33:55,549
Take the win and go home.

508
00:33:55,549 --> 00:33:57,990
Ok, I'm gonna go out there,
tell them Monica killed you.

509
00:33:57,990 --> 00:34:01,466
- I wish you wouldn't.
- Why? Because it's true?

510
00:34:01,466 --> 00:34:04,509
Because he loves her.

511
00:34:04,509 --> 00:34:06,559
And because it isn't true.

512
00:34:07,768 --> 00:34:11,098
You know, Mr. Gregory,
I am gonna be honest with you.

513
00:34:11,098 --> 00:34:13,949
The more time I spend with you,
the less I seem to like you.

514
00:34:14,703 --> 00:34:19,902
But you are my first real
for profit visitation from the other side,

515
00:34:19,902 --> 00:34:22,355
So that counts for something.

516
00:34:22,355 --> 00:34:25,205
I am gonna ask you one more time.

517
00:34:25,205 --> 00:34:29,173
If it isn't Henry Alonso,
and it isn't your son's fiance, then who?

518
00:34:33,824 --> 00:34:39,324
- Did Wesley know about the two of you?
- There was no two of us.

519
00:34:39,324 --> 00:34:42,955
I thought my son was weak, feckless.

520
00:34:42,955 --> 00:34:45,204
I was trying to protect him.

521
00:34:45,204 --> 00:34:47,861
By seducing his girlfriend.

522
00:34:47,861 --> 00:34:51,196
I thought I had to prove something to him.

523
00:34:51,196 --> 00:34:54,631
About his girlfriend's character.

524
00:34:54,631 --> 00:34:59,417
Instead, I found something else about his.

525
00:34:59,417 --> 00:35:04,284
She told him, didn't she?
She told Wesley that you tried.

526
00:35:04,284 --> 00:35:06,841
One of the real secrets of
my success and business,

527
00:35:06,841 --> 00:35:10,998
has always been my ability to sell anything,

528
00:35:10,998 --> 00:35:15,017
almost anything to,
almost anyone and anytime.

529
00:35:15,017 --> 00:35:18,117
But I could not convince that boy.

530
00:35:18,117 --> 00:35:21,558
That the girl he is in love with, was lying.

531
00:35:22,644 --> 00:35:27,153
Oh, my God.
He did it.

532
00:35:27,905 --> 00:35:30,239
Your own son.

533
00:35:32,464 --> 00:35:38,749
I honestly can't even
begin to describe you
that collision of emotions, I mean.

534
00:35:38,749 --> 00:35:40,640
You are staring at your own death.

535
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:43,694
And yet, I didn't think
he had them in him.

536
00:35:43,694 --> 00:35:47,320
I mean, the way
he made it look like robbery.

537
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:50,351
Take my watch and ring,
and throw them in that dumpster.

538
00:35:50,351 --> 00:35:52,746
I am not sure I could
have come up with that.

539
00:35:52,746 --> 00:35:55,503
I am gonna have to
tell him, you know that.

540
00:35:56,953 --> 00:36:01,220
Seven four two zero five.

541
00:36:02,379 --> 00:36:06,475
What? / That's half the routing
number of an account in a bank in Malaga

542
00:36:06,475 --> 00:36:09,223
You'll get the other half,
when you arrive in Spain.

543
00:36:09,223 --> 00:36:14,234
There's exactly $349,000 in that account,
I'm the only one who knows about it.

544
00:36:15,267 --> 00:36:17,825
That's enough for you to start having a real life.

545
00:36:17,825 --> 00:36:20,413
To make something of yourself.

546
00:36:20,413 --> 00:36:25,353
Just.. let a father give his son in death

547
00:36:25,353 --> 00:36:27,953
What he couldn't in life.

548
00:36:27,953 --> 00:36:30,210
And let this innocent man go to jail.

549
00:36:30,210 --> 00:36:34,998
The question here isn't about Henry Alonso

550
00:36:34,998 --> 00:36:37,926
It's about Michael Benoit.

551
00:36:37,926 --> 00:36:40,634
Is he going to walk away from
this experience as a rich man?

552
00:36:40,634 --> 00:36:44,841
Or is he going back to work
at that 900 phone lines.

553
00:36:52,465 --> 00:36:55,777
Mrs. Ubershire.

554
00:36:55,777 --> 00:37:00,233
- Joe Dubois, we met the other day.
- Ah, yes, of course.

555
00:37:00,233 --> 00:37:02,605
What can I do for you, Mr. Dubois?

556
00:37:02,605 --> 00:37:05,769
Well, I was just wondering
how do you like you car.

557
00:37:05,769 --> 00:37:09,812
Because I really love mine,
I love everything about it.
Even the color is perfect.

558
00:37:09,812 --> 00:37:12,837
You went for the metallic brown too,
didn't you?

559
00:37:12,837 --> 00:37:16,926
Is there something I can
help you with, Mr. Dubois?

560
00:37:19,009 --> 00:37:22,812
Well, I am guessing Ubershire
isn't the most common of names.

561
00:37:22,812 --> 00:37:26,088
Would it surprise you to learn that we got one
living on our street?

562
00:37:26,088 --> 00:37:30,022
I, myself didn't know until I check with
my neighbourhood watch this morning.

563
00:37:30,022 --> 00:37:33,178
Glaudis Ubershire,
she moved in a few months ago.

564
00:37:33,178 --> 00:37:36,160
Just a couple of doors down from our house.

565
00:37:36,160 --> 00:37:39,335
I went over to
introduce myself
this morning,
and then..

566
00:37:39,335 --> 00:37:42,418
It turns out she's got a sister-in-law
who teaches at this school.

567
00:37:42,418 --> 00:37:45,657
Yeah, the sister-in-law came over for dinner
last Sunday night

568
00:37:45,657 --> 00:37:51,796
Same night, somebody smashed
the window of mine.
Metallic brown '04 Jeep Cherokee

569
00:37:51,796 --> 00:37:54,000
You got it mixed up, right?

570
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:58,005
You tried to put your key in my jeep,
and then when the door wouldn't open,

571
00:37:58,005 --> 00:38:01,741
You broke the window to get inside.

572
00:38:01,741 --> 00:38:04,807
You probably didn't even figure out
your mistake until

573
00:38:04,807 --> 00:38:07,895
the key wouldn't work
in the ignition, either.

574
00:38:09,415 --> 00:38:12,225
Here, this is the bill

575
00:38:12,225 --> 00:38:15,147
What it costed me to fix the window
that you smashed.

576
00:38:15,147 --> 00:38:19,608
All the time, all the upset,
it's on the house.

577
00:38:19,608 --> 00:38:24,217
You.. you actually expect me to pay that?

578
00:38:24,217 --> 00:38:28,767
A parents' job, Mrs. Ubershire,
is to listen to their child.

579
00:38:28,767 --> 00:38:32,663
Bridgette is telling me that
I ought to go to the police on this.

580
00:38:32,663 --> 00:38:35,438
Maybe she is right about that, too.

581
00:38:39,612 --> 00:38:42,485
Hey, official secret police psychic.

582
00:38:44,475 --> 00:38:47,513
Can I ask you a question?

583
00:38:48,177 --> 00:38:50,674
How are we gonna get
Henry Alonso out of the jail?

584
00:38:52,346 --> 00:38:55,923
Mr. King, I was starting to worry
you weren't gonna make it. / Sorry.

585
00:38:55,923 --> 00:38:59,137
I was.. in a meeting with some of
the partners of my dad's company,

586
00:38:59,137 --> 00:39:02,989
Trying to figure out where
I fit in the new hierarchy.

587
00:39:04,254 --> 00:39:06,652
You said that the district attorney
had some questions for me.

588
00:39:06,652 --> 00:39:09,494
He is just finishing up with
someone in the conference room.

589
00:39:09,494 --> 00:39:11,374
This way.

590
00:39:19,010 --> 00:39:21,795
Monica?

591
00:39:21,795 --> 00:39:25,091
Oh.. I'm so sorry, Wes.

592
00:39:25,091 --> 00:39:28,761
They knew everything.
I couldn't lie.

593
00:39:28,761 --> 00:39:31,852
I don't understand
what you are talking about.

594
00:39:32,569 --> 00:39:35,585
- Monica!
- I'm sorry. / Monica!

595
00:39:35,585 --> 00:39:37,336
What did you tell them?

596
00:39:39,621 --> 00:39:42,021
Does someone please want to tell me
what the hell is going on here?

597
00:39:42,021 --> 00:39:45,038
Your fiance was just
telling us about the night
your father tried to seduce her.

598
00:39:45,038 --> 00:39:49,317
She said she came
clean with you about it
just hours before he was killed.

599
00:39:49,317 --> 00:39:54,242
I guess she just decided
she'd rather have a clear conscience than
being accessory to murder.

600
00:39:55,446 --> 00:39:57,292
Now, if you wouldn't mind, Mr. King,

601
00:39:57,292 --> 00:39:59,838
we have a lot,
we would like to discuss it with you.

602
00:40:05,157 --> 00:40:07,165
Excuse me. Wesley?
Can we have a
statement right here please?

603
00:40:09,216 --> 00:40:11,551
What a waste.

604
00:40:16,143 --> 00:40:20,100
- You're still here.
- I gave that boy everything.

605
00:40:20,100 --> 00:40:23,395
I tried to make him a man,
here he is.. blubbering to the cops.

606
00:40:23,395 --> 00:40:28,137
Well, if it's any consolation,
my sister says he'll probably get a manslaughter.

607
00:40:28,137 --> 00:40:31,534
Yeah, with good behavior, five years?

608
00:40:31,534 --> 00:40:35,077
Yeah, right.
Knowing him, he would be a model prisoner.

609
00:40:35,077 --> 00:40:37,454
And you. You're no better.

610
00:40:37,454 --> 00:40:40,254
I offered you a
chance of a whole new life,

611
00:40:40,254 --> 00:40:41,997
I hope you are happy.

612
00:40:44,449 --> 00:40:46,246
Actually, I am.

